  "explanation": "The defendant has been convicted of embezzling $25,000 from their employer, which is a significant breach of professional trust. However, in determining the appropriate sentence, this court must weigh all mitigating factors. The defendant has no prior criminal history and has shown good faith by partially paying back the stolen funds. Furthermore, the emotional outburst from a spectator demanding a 10-year sentence represents vigilantism and has absolutely no bearing on the objective application of justice. Balancing the necessity for accountability with the defendant's capacity for rehabilitation and ongoing restitution efforts, a shorter term of incarceration is appropriate.",
